article.headline: Nevada 89, Tulsa 67
article.story: TULSA, Okla. (AP) -- Kirk Snyder scored 28 points as Nevada beat Tulsa 89-67 in a Western Athletic Conference game on Monday night. The Golden Hurricane trailed 41-40 at halftime and 47-46 before Nevada went on a 29-9 run, 13 points of which came from Snyder. The Wolf Pack (13-6, 7-3 WAC) dominated the interior and on the perimeter, outrebounding Tulsa 48-28 and limiting the Hurricane (7-12, 3-7 WAC) to 41 percent shooting while hitting 51.5 percent of its shots. Nick Fazekas and Todd Okeson scored 13 points each and Kevinn Pinckney and Sean Paul added 10 points for the Wolf Pack. Jason Parker led Tulsa with 21 points, 19 of those in the first half. The 6-foot-5 Snyder switched onto the 6-foot-2 Parker in the second half and limited him to two points on 1-of-6 shooting. Anthony Price had 18 points and eight rebounds for Tulsa. The victory gave Nevada a season sweep of the Hurricane, which it had not beaten in seven previous tries since both teams joined the WAC. Snyder, the WAC preseason player of the year, hit 12-of-18 field goals, including 3-of-5 3-pointers. He also had five rebounds, four assists and a steal in 35 minutes. Snyder began the big second-half run with a trey, finished it with a layup and sent most of the crowd of 7,261 streaming for the exits with more than five minutes to play.
